{"answer_uniqueness_state":{"approval":null,"status":"pending"},"artifact_id":"q-sap-org-04-account-boundaries","artifact_type":"question","author":{"identity":"openai-codex-sap-org-04-content-author","identity_type":"model","role":"lesson_question_author"},"blueprint_references":[{"blueprint_id":"aws-sap-c02-assessment-blueprint","canonical_digest":"3362d465a410c84d40250cd3b6dcfa5ac80cfc25d0b8d7b034b45327b8049d8d","version":"0.3A.1"}],"canonical_digest":"94d1b6a0b2d91e41e9b244e40102061d9c9736ab56cee17b9e61a423d291b008","content_review_state":{"approval":null,"status":"pending"},"created_at":"2026-07-19T21:30:00Z","keyed_option_ids":["a"],"learner_explanation":"Option A is best because it keeps ordinary workloads in member accounts, uses OUs as account groupings for shared policy requirements, and adds only the hierarchy justified by a distinct baseline. Option B conflicts with AWS management-account guidance and cannot rely on SCPs to constrain management-account identities. Option C preserves accounts but repeats controls and adds hierarchy that the scenario does not require. Option D is structurally wrong because OUs group accounts, not resources inside an account.","modified_at":"2026-07-20T00:41:00Z","objective_references":{"primary":"SAP-ORG-04","supporting":["SAP-FND-01","SAP-FND-02","SAP-ORG-02"]},"option_rationales":[{"category":"key_support","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ou-policy-target","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"079e74a58fe39b16084f8ff9bff68564c89655dff153e1535d7f06083f2bb359","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-rec-control-aligned-ous","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"9792d6f6edf5753fd069b146c7bf1d87ecb5ec40d65874b5827aed3dea29b3f4","revision":4},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-rec-isolate-management","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"2040756b2ed4bd2c800cb7e0607825dc6cffd259df2a9227fd13b841638acf31","revision":3}],"is_keyed":true,"option_id":"a","rationale":"It satisfies all four requirements with the smallest justified hierarchy.","requirement_ids":["req-isolation","req-controls","req-growth","req-overhead"]},{"category":"inappropriate_boundary","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-management-resource-guidance","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"c61e5b3182089a0941651717a2435de03d5a414fa84494a41f9a81e13bc45b7e","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-management-scp-gap","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"e3312344d277a0092d87441d6ee327c092d452e2ee76e4adf5d2a0d873fe29af","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-rec-isolate-management","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"2040756b2ed4bd2c800cb7e0607825dc6cffd259df2a9227fd13b841638acf31","revision":3}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"b","rationale":"It places ordinary workloads in the management account despite the explicit absence of a management-only need.","requirement_ids":["req-isolation"]},{"category":"excessive_operational_burden","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ou-control-guidance","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"86f2550e06e9536a6bde3890f17fe3b6bfe0ac67058c70200c5ad0589e4ea099","revision":2},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-rec-control-aligned-ous","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"9792d6f6edf5753fd069b146c7bf1d87ecb5ec40d65874b5827aed3dea29b3f4","revision":4}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"c","rationale":"It duplicates controls account by account and introduces hierarchy unrelated to the stated control baselines.","requirement_ids":["req-controls","req-overhead"]},{"category":"inappropriate_boundary","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ou-policy-target","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"079e74a58fe39b16084f8ff9bff68564c89655dff153e1535d7f06083f2bb359","revision":1}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"d","rationale":"It uses a member account but does not create separate account groupings to which the three distinct organization-policy baselines can be applied.","requirement_ids":["req-controls","req-growth"]}],"options":[{"option_id":"a","text":"Place production and development in separate member accounts, group accounts into shallow OUs by shared control baseline, apply common organization policies at the OU level, and add a distinct OU only when the regulated baseline is introduced."},{"option_id":"b","text":"Place all workloads in the management account and separate production, development, and regulated resources with tags and IAM roles."},{"option_id":"c","text":"Create member accounts but mirror every reporting team with a deep OU branch, then configure equivalent controls separately on every account."},{"option_id":"d","text":"Use one member account for all workloads and use resource tags to distinguish the three control baselines."}],"originality_review_state":{"review":null,"status":"pending"},"question_id":"q-sap-org-04-account-boundaries","question_type":"single_response","required_selection_count":1,"requirement_option_matrix":[{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"req-isolation"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"d","result":"fails"}],"requirement_id":"req-controls"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"d","result":"fails"}],"requirement_id":"req-growth"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"c","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"req-overhead"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"c","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"con-no-universal-tree"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"con-management"}],"revision":5,"schema_version":"ala.authoring.question.v1","source_citation_projection":[{"canonical_digest":"603a5aac9c45c132aa8620478878cc7c9bbc17ccf4718bb99a18c9f1b4c1c12e","locator":"Avoid deploying workloads to the organization's management account","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-management-account"},{"canonical_digest":"e85654f27aa4dd36eb8c6ea2773b0c0c6bfca449c934785280a18fe1e5ad3baf","locator":"Recommended foundational organizational unit (OUs); Understanding AWS Organizations","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-ou-practices"},{"canonical_digest":"2bb881d43a5a2f516f52c7122b0dde356cf92e23d7450d7b3897ef9d19f42a2b","locator":"SCPs don't affect users or roles in the management account","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-scps"}],"specification_reference":{"artifact_id":"qspec-sap-org-04-account-boundaries","artifact_type":"question_spec","canonical_digest":"3c64e512b4116f4c82df8b2679a482bf7768f9be0b01206b8c846f78e766163c","revision":1},"status":"active","stem":"A company is moving ordinary production and development workloads into an AWS organization. Production and development require different control baselines. A future regulated workload will require a third baseline. No workload requires a management-account-only function. Teams should retain ownership inside their accounts, and the company wants the least repeated control administration. Which design best meets these requirements?","supersedes":{"artifact_id":"q-sap-org-04-account-boundaries","artifact_type":"question","canonical_digest":"5c73d1d4f6618d60a3c940be9ef774db459e745b4a10075ed91d094216d92830","revision":4},"supporting_claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-management-resource-guidance","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"c61e5b3182089a0941651717a2435de03d5a414fa84494a41f9a81e13bc45b7e","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-management-scp-gap","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"e3312344d277a0092d87441d6ee327c092d452e2ee76e4adf5d2a0d873fe29af","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ou-control-guidance","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"86f2550e06e9536a6bde3890f17fe3b6bfe0ac67058c70200c5ad0589e4ea099","revision":2},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ou-policy-target","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"079e74a58fe39b16084f8ff9bff68564c89655dff153e1535d7f06083f2bb359","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-rec-control-aligned-ous","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"9792d6f6edf5753fd069b146c7bf1d87ecb5ec40d65874b5827aed3dea29b3f4","revision":4},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-rec-isolate-management","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"2040756b2ed4bd2c800cb7e0607825dc6cffd259df2a9227fd13b841638acf31","revision":3}],"validation_state":{"report":null,"status":"not_run"}}
